ab38a2028fef1d54c77d9f2de9e3c9b986e7d80a.commit.message:
To prevent wiki paths that have space prefixes from being interpreted as inter-wiki links,  JSPWikiMarkupParser prioritizes these first. This means that that wiki space names can't be the same as those for an interwiki prefixes. (Which is ok: when you think about it, an outside wiki is really just a space managed by someone else.) This fix was needed prevent various unit tests from bombing.

b63c80fb3469ffd3797f3288a10176f4a2b9738b.commit.message:
Added method WikiEngine.beautify(WikiPath), which works identically to the String version, except that those paths who are prefixed with the default space name (plus a colon) are rendered without the space name. WikiEngine also gains a method getSpaces(), which today only returns the default space. In the future this will be configurable.

c95a23e073a30b6df29e0795bf06b000147b6ee4.commit.message:
Second commit of ReferenceManager. All unit tests now pass, although certain behaviors are slightly different than in the past. In particular, the WikiPaths passed to getReferredBy() and getRefersTo() are NOT resolved; they are assumed to be correct. This was an unnecessary optimization that, in practice, was not needed. Overall pass rate over 93%.
